<br>
I pulled a few too many last night and though they were not hitting me too hard I thought the MOB would have went down faster if I had DS on me.<br>
<br>
Just a question for all you &quot;Ubers out there&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fenobleu@themagicianstower>Fenobleu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 6:43:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=425.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using Damage Shield</span><hr size=1> Not sure what level you are but beyond a certain point you do not want to be getting hit - mob damage output is just too high for anything like the number of hits you would have to take to justify the DS.<br>
<br>
However, DSing yourself to get improved fire resistance can be very handy at times.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=368916">Fenobleu Wayfarer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
42nd level Mage, Brell Serilis</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fenobleu@themagicianstower>Fenobleu</A> at: 10/29/02 6:43:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nitramro>nitramro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 6:14:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=425.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thanks</span><hr size=1> I am level 34 and was in Najena doing the focus quest so mobs are low and was getting hit by lots of fire spells so was wondering if this was a viable way to use DS<br>
<br>
Thanks for responding<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 717<br> <font color=#333333>(10/31/02 5:04:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=425.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> Up to about level 39 or so, it is worth it to ds yourself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bandose>Bandose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/02 11:40:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=425.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> My experience in self DSing would dictate NO, do not bother DSing yourself unless you have KEI or something where mana isn't an issue.  At lower lvls, KEI lets you kill almost red mobs easily and almost never run out of mana, as your spells don't use much mana compared to the casting time and KEI's regen.<br>
<br>
The two problems with the mage DS need to be taken into consideration.  First, our DS lasts about half as long as a Druid DS.  Length of buff time usually doens't play a factor when doing one fight, however if you need to DS before EVERY fight, you're gonna be using a lot of mana for the small amount of damage it does.<br>
<br>
The most drastic problem is after about lvl 40, you do NOT want to be hit.  YOU WILL DIE since most of these mobs can hit for 100+.  Since most of these mobs have the capability to double, the most damage you'll do is 36 points (lvl 39 DS) and you'll take 200+ points damage.  That's not a fair trade when you realize you can use that 100 mana to do a lvl 20 heal for 220 HPs or nuke it with the lvl 24 Shock of Spikes nuke for 176 points of damage (for 110 mana).<br>
<br>
The ONLY real reason to be within melee range is to get your defense skills maxed.  It's nice to also have your offense skills maxed, but it isn't as important as your ability to avoid damage at higher lvls.<br>
<br>
If your desired end result is a faster kill, use your nukes.  If it's to work up skills, use that mana to buff yourself and pet and remeber, if you get too low on HPs, your pet can NOT keep the mob off you.  In other words, if you melee, KEEP GATE READY. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=talusini>Talusini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www3.sympatico.ca/talusar/magician.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(11/11/02 1:55:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=425.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/talusar/Talusini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using Damage Shield</span><hr size=1> Before I got my epic, I used to ALWAYS DS my pet when soloing...but that's just me.  I used to use the multipet earth technique. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=411018&amp;resize=true&quot;" target="_new">Talusini Petuccini</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Mage - Master of the Elements<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pbf.mightye.org?&amp;resize=true&quot;" target="_new">Peace by Force</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=p644kd>p644kd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 9:10:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=425.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using Damage Shield</span><hr size=1> Hey,<br>
<br>
The only mob I have found so far worth casting a DS while soloing are the needites in Echo Caverns. They hit multiple times for little damage and literaly kill themselves on a damage shield. A mage with a fire pet can solo the whole room clear in a few miniutes. <br>
<br>
